WABCO Holdings Inc. Key Developments

ZF Friedrichshafen And WABCO Reportedly In Merger Talks
Jul 25 17
ZF Friedrichshafen AG recently held advanced takeover talks with WABCO Holdings Inc. (NYSE:WBC) before they fell apart amid resistance from ZF’s board. Wabco disclosed when it reported second-quarter earnings last week that it had received a takeover offer from an unnamed party; according to people familiar with the matter, ZF is the mystery bidder. It isn’t clear whether ZF could return with another bid, and according to people familiar with the matter it’s possible Wabco could draw another suitor. 


WABCO Holdings Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Revises Earnings Guidance for Full Year 2017
Jul 20 17
WABCO Holdings Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported sales of $795.0 million compared to $732.2 million a year ago. Operating income was $108.4 million compared to $103.9 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $105.5 million compared to $99.3 million a year ago. Net income attributable to company was $87.2 million or $1.61 per diluted share compared to $75.1 million or $1.33 per diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $88.2 million compared to $114.8 million a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment were $22.3 million compared to $20.4 million a year ago. Adjusted Operating Income was $119.6 million against $109.9 million a year ago. EBIT was $105.3 million against $98.5 million a year ago. 

For the six months, the company reported sales of $1,542.3 million compared to $1,420.8 million a year ago. Operating income was $216.9 million compared to $196.5 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $205.1 million compared to $190.6 million a year ago. Net income attributable to company was $167.9 million or $3.09 per diluted share compared to $61.7 million or $1.09 per diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $142.5 million compared to $208.0 million a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment were $35.6 million compared to $46.9 million a year ago. Adjusted Operating Income was $234.3 million against $211.1 million a year ago. EBIT was $205.1 million against $189.2 million a year ago. 

The company upgraded sales guidance for full year 2017 to now range from $3,205 million to $3,100 million against previous guidance from $2,850 million to $2,990 million. The company upgraded reported diluted EPS guidance for full year 2017 to now range from $5.74 to $6.04 against previous guidance from $5.44 to $5.94; and performance full year 2016 diluted EPS to now range from $6.05 to $6.35 against previous guidance from $5.55 to $6.05. U.S. GAAP tax rate is forecasted just below 16%.


WABCO Holdings Inc. to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 20, 2017
Jul 20 17
WABCO Holdings Inc. announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results on Jul 20, 2017


